ProtoDefines:
. "If $f$ is locally integrable on $(a,b]$, we define $$ 
   \int_a^b f(x)\,dx=\lim_{c\to a+}\int_c^b f(x)\,dx $$ 
   provided that the limit exists (finite). To include the case
   where $a=-\infty$, we adopt the convention that 
   $-\infty+=-\infty$."
